                "institute": "1USATAM"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The experiment was performed at the",
                "Cyclotron Institute of the Texas A&M University using",
                "the K500 cyclotron"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "1-H-2",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.98
              },
              "free_text": [
                " isotopically enriched deuterated",
                "polyethylene CD2 targets with a thickness in the range",
                "400-800 mu-g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The TECSA array made up of 8 YY1-300 Micron",
                "detectors (each one with 16 arch strips), was set at",
                "190mm from target covering angles in the range",
                " 15-40 deg was optimized for the alpha particle",
                "detection."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 15O ions were detected using two position",
                "sensitive detectors (PSD, type X1,16 strips each),",
                "placed symmetrically at 340mm and covering angles",
                "from 15O = 3deg - 12. deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "18F beam was produced via the p(18O,18F)n reaction,",
                "after energy degrading of the primary beam by means",
                "of an Al degrader (around 30 mu-m thick).After",
                "isotopic selection the obtained secondary beam was",
                "tuned through MARS with a final energy of 52MeV on a",
                "position sensitive detector at the target location of",
                "TECSA"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TROJA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " In adopted Trojan Horse Method the method is",
                "based on the quasifree deuteron breakup, where",
                "deuteron breaks up into participant particle p and",
                "spectator particle n. Here the 18F(d,alpha n) 15-O",
                "measurement was performed to obtain information on",
                "18F(p,alpha) 15-O cross section at energies relevant",
                "for astrophysics. FRom measured cross sections reaction",
                "rarts for 18F(p,alpha)15-O was determined"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence between alpha particles and 15-O",
                "ions was required. Neutrons were undetected and their",
                "momentum distribution was inferred from"
              ]
            }
          ],
